data.name: Spicy Mexican Bean Chili
data.quickTastyDescription: A hearty and flavorful chili packed with beans, spices, and a kick of heat, perfect for a cozy meal any night.
detailedCookingInstructions: Heat olive oil in a pot over medium heat.
Add chopped onion and bell pepper; sauté until softened, about 5 minutes.
Stir in the garlic powder, onion powder, chili powder, cumin, and diced jalapeño (if using); cook for another minute.
Add the canned black beans, kidney beans, and diced tomatoes (with their juice) to the pot.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and let simmer for about 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Season with salt to taste, and serve hot.
